1
00:00:35,076 --> 00:00:36,995
I wish I had superpowers,

2
00:00:37,078 --> 00:00:38,496
so I could stop the world.

3
00:00:38,580 --> 00:00:41,166
<i>Because what matters to me</i>
<i>is the two of us.</i>

4
00:00:41,249 --> 00:00:43,001
We have each other anyway.

5
00:00:43,084 --> 00:00:45,295
<i>If you're not ready to face the world yet,</i>

6
00:00:45,378 --> 00:00:47,172
we can run away from it.

7
00:00:53,553 --> 00:00:54,763
<i>Starting today,</i>

8
00:00:54,846 --> 00:00:58,933
Mikoy is now considered
an enemy of the state.

9
00:00:59,017 --> 00:01:02,771
This is basically a shoot-to-kill order
in the eyes of covert operators.

10
00:01:13,073 --> 00:01:15,492
Mikoy, didn't I tell you?

11
00:01:17,202 --> 00:01:18,828
<i>You can't take a different route.</i>

12
00:01:18,912 --> 00:01:20,622
<i>We have to stick to the same routine.</i>

13
00:01:20,705 --> 00:01:22,749
<i>Otherwise, you'll stand out.</i>

14
00:01:22,832 --> 00:01:25,043
I just had to stop somewhere earlier.

15
00:01:34,052 --> 00:01:36,888
<i>You have no idea how happy I am.</i>

16
00:01:43,561 --> 00:01:46,147
Do you know where our child is?

17
00:01:47,690 --> 00:01:51,986
Maybe she's already in Cebu
with our future in-laws.

18
00:01:56,825 --> 00:02:01,704
Clearly, they know something
about what's going on.

19
00:02:02,288 --> 00:02:06,543
Then, let's reach out to them
more aggressively.

20
00:02:07,168 --> 00:02:09,546
Let's send a grand emissary.

21
00:02:19,681 --> 00:02:21,141
Oh, wow!

22
00:02:21,224 --> 00:02:22,600
Looking sharp!

23
00:02:22,684 --> 00:02:23,893
Is it your JS Prom?

24
00:02:24,477 --> 00:02:25,478
You look old.

25
00:02:25,562 --> 00:02:27,230
Do you know these two?

26
00:02:28,022 --> 00:02:31,025
Hold on, bro. It's blurry.
I cannot see it.

27
00:02:31,109 --> 00:02:34,112
I'll give you some money
to get your eyes checked.

28
00:02:34,195 --> 00:02:37,532
Hold on. Let me call my friends.
It'll be easier to see.

29
00:02:38,992 --> 00:02:39,826
BARANGAY POLICE

30
00:02:41,161 --> 00:02:42,912
Someone's looking for brother Mikoy.

31
00:02:42,996 --> 00:02:44,038
Lookouts!

32
00:03:03,266 --> 00:03:05,310
He's looking for Mikoy.

33
00:03:05,977 --> 00:03:07,395
Why are you looking for Mikoy?

34
00:03:14,235 --> 00:03:18,865
I got nothing,
but a hospital bill for our man.

35
00:03:20,408 --> 00:03:21,409
You know what, Bok?

36
00:03:22,577 --> 00:03:25,371
What Sir Norberto
was trying to say is right.

37
00:03:25,455 --> 00:03:28,541
With all of Mikoy's knowledge
about the agency's secrets,

38
00:03:29,167 --> 00:03:32,420
I won't be surprised if he becomes
the enemy of the state

39
00:03:32,503 --> 00:03:34,839
in the eyes of the higher-ups.

40
00:03:34,923 --> 00:03:36,257
Of course, it will be that way.

41
00:03:36,341 --> 00:03:40,094
I won't be surprised if he
is taken down by the law operatives

42
00:03:40,178 --> 00:03:41,804
because he's considered a traitor now.

43
00:03:42,972 --> 00:03:44,390
We're already there.

44
00:03:44,474 --> 00:03:47,101
But do you really think
Mikoy would betray us?

45
00:03:51,314 --> 00:03:53,691
Looks like our guy
was simply blinded by love.

46
00:03:53,775 --> 00:03:55,652
That's why he ran away with Chiara.

47
00:03:57,070 --> 00:03:59,614
Whatever Mikoy's reason may be,

48
00:03:59,697 --> 00:04:02,617
we need to find him immediately.

49
00:04:05,328 --> 00:04:06,454
You're right.

50
00:04:06,537 --> 00:04:08,039
The warrant of arrest

51
00:04:08,122 --> 00:04:11,668
is enough to be tantamount
to a shoot-to-kill order.

52
00:04:12,418 --> 00:04:15,171
No matter how immoral and illegal it is.

53
00:04:18,007 --> 00:04:19,217
Thank you.

54
00:04:19,968 --> 00:04:22,345
Thank you, Bok, for supporting me.

55
00:04:23,888 --> 00:04:24,764
I mean,

56
00:04:25,515 --> 00:04:27,809
General Norberto is right.

57
00:04:29,060 --> 00:04:31,062
You're the one who had
the most doubts about Mikoy.

58
00:04:32,021 --> 00:04:33,773
But even so,

59
00:04:34,357 --> 00:04:38,486
you still believe that we need
to find and save him.

60
00:04:39,737 --> 00:04:40,613
Well.

61
00:04:42,740 --> 00:04:45,201
Who else would support you here?

62
00:04:46,286 --> 00:04:47,453
It's just me.

63
00:04:55,420 --> 00:04:57,338
There's only one place where

64
00:04:57,422 --> 00:04:59,549
I think they know where Mikoy is.

65
00:05:14,939 --> 00:05:18,776
How could they not know each other when
they've been connected since childhood?

66
00:05:18,860 --> 00:05:20,445
They've joined forces
since they were young.

67
00:05:20,528 --> 00:05:23,448
They're godfathers, godmothers,
and compadres.

68
00:05:23,531 --> 00:05:26,326
That's how it is in the Philippines.
That's how Filipinos are.

69
00:05:31,164 --> 00:05:33,624
They're scrutinizing outsiders.

70
00:05:41,299 --> 00:05:45,178
And La Morte Bianca
wants us to stay quiet for now.

71
00:05:45,261 --> 00:05:47,972
The solution is simple.

72
00:05:48,056 --> 00:05:49,766
Let's show up there ourselves,

73
00:05:49,849 --> 00:05:52,268
reach out, and make an appearance,

74
00:05:52,351 --> 00:05:54,979
show them we're being genuine.

75
00:06:13,748 --> 00:06:15,583
Come to think of it,

76
00:06:15,666 --> 00:06:20,129
why has Agent Sianong
been so supportive recently?

77
00:06:20,963 --> 00:06:22,548
Back then, when it came to Mikoy,

78
00:06:22,632 --> 00:06:26,010
he was like a constant devil's advocate.

79
00:06:26,636 --> 00:06:29,430
Dara, can't you see?

80
00:06:29,514 --> 00:06:33,476
So much chaos has already happened
in this office, in our agency.

81
00:06:33,559 --> 00:06:37,146
Now is the time when we need unity.

82
00:06:37,230 --> 00:06:40,525
That unity talk is nonsense.
No one believes that anymore.

83
00:06:40,608 --> 00:06:42,068
Just admit it.

84
00:06:43,402 --> 00:06:45,321
You have hidden feelings.

85
00:06:45,404 --> 00:06:46,322
Hey!

86
00:06:48,241 --> 00:06:49,951
Cut it out.

87
00:06:53,412 --> 00:06:55,456
Dara, take her back to the hospital.

88
00:06:55,540 --> 00:06:56,916
You can't order me around.

89
00:06:56,999 --> 00:06:59,460
And I won't let the person
I love disappear again.

90
00:07:00,962 --> 00:07:03,756
"And I won't let the person
I love disappear again."

91
00:07:04,715 --> 00:07:06,425
Then he walks out.

92
00:07:07,343 --> 00:07:08,386
Why?

93
00:07:09,846 --> 00:07:11,305
It's true.

94
00:07:11,389 --> 00:07:12,932
I love Agent Alex.

95
00:07:13,850 --> 00:07:15,685
I love you, too.

96
00:07:15,768 --> 00:07:18,020
Rafa, Kian, and General Norberto too.

97
00:07:18,104 --> 00:07:20,189
I love everyone in this office.

98
00:07:20,273 --> 00:07:21,566
I'm just a loving person.

99
00:07:21,649 --> 00:07:23,734
Tell that to your grandmother.

100
00:07:23,818 --> 00:07:26,320
For a covert government agent,

101
00:07:26,404 --> 00:07:28,281
you're not very good at lying.

102
00:07:28,364 --> 00:07:30,450
Hey, Agent Sianong.

103
00:07:30,533 --> 00:07:32,535
I've watched so many K-dramas.

104
00:07:32,618 --> 00:07:35,413
I practically have
a doctoral degree majoring

105
00:07:35,496 --> 00:07:38,374
in second lead syndrome.

106
00:07:43,463 --> 00:07:46,340
That's why I know that deep inside,

107
00:07:46,424 --> 00:07:49,927
you really think it's better
if Mikoy is out of the picture.

108
00:07:50,011 --> 00:07:51,554
If it's your choice,

109
00:07:51,637 --> 00:07:54,640
maybe it'd be better
if he was never found.

110
00:07:58,436 --> 00:08:01,898
You know, if you were a Fishbook ad,

111
00:08:01,981 --> 00:08:04,108
I wouldn't even wait three seconds,
let alone five,

112
00:08:04,192 --> 00:08:05,193
I'd skip you right away.

113
00:08:05,276 --> 00:08:06,736
You talk too much.

114
00:08:08,529 --> 00:08:10,156
You're so defensive!

115
00:08:12,366 --> 00:08:15,203
You know, it's a good thing
Madam gave us permission.

116
00:08:15,286 --> 00:08:17,163
Even though it's not our day off yet.

117
00:08:17,747 --> 00:08:20,416
Maybe she's happy with us.

118
00:08:21,209 --> 00:08:22,418
Maybe.

119
00:08:23,461 --> 00:08:26,464
Wait. Are you hungry, sweetheart?

120
00:08:26,547 --> 00:08:28,341
Yes, let's eat!

121
00:08:28,424 --> 00:08:29,425
Let's go.

122
00:08:43,439 --> 00:08:44,815
Ouch!

123
00:08:47,318 --> 00:08:48,152
You go ahead.

124
00:08:48,236 --> 00:08:50,196
- No.
- It's okay.

125
00:08:54,992 --> 00:08:57,912
Don't cry. We're going to get ice cream.

126
00:09:04,919 --> 00:09:06,212
Hey.

127
00:09:06,796 --> 00:09:07,922
You.

128
00:09:08,798 --> 00:09:11,175
They just look so happy.

129
00:09:12,134 --> 00:09:13,594
Why?

130
00:09:13,678 --> 00:09:15,429
Do you want that, too?

131
00:09:18,307 --> 00:09:20,560
I do, but…

132
00:09:21,602 --> 00:09:23,062
Why is there a but?

133
00:09:25,273 --> 00:09:27,149
It just feels impossible.

134
00:09:27,858 --> 00:09:29,527
Come on, sweetheart.

135
00:09:29,610 --> 00:09:31,696
Always remember this, okay?

136
00:09:31,779 --> 00:09:33,906
Everything is possible.

137
00:09:40,538 --> 00:09:41,914
Oh, you.

138
00:09:41,998 --> 00:09:43,374
Look at it.

139
00:09:43,457 --> 00:09:47,044
We're here in Hong Kong together.

140
00:09:47,128 --> 00:09:48,296
Can you imagine that?

141
00:09:48,379 --> 00:09:50,089
Our relationship survived,

142
00:09:50,172 --> 00:09:52,508
despite all the secrets and pretending.

143
00:09:53,342 --> 00:09:56,304
Because our love is real.

144
00:09:57,972 --> 00:10:01,434
That's why to me, no matter what happens,

145
00:10:01,517 --> 00:10:03,936
there's always a tomorrow waiting for us.

146
00:10:05,187 --> 00:10:08,649
And I'm so excited for our future.

147
00:10:09,191 --> 00:10:12,862
I can face any tomorrow
as long as you're with me.

148
00:10:12,945 --> 00:10:14,697
That's it!

149
00:10:14,780 --> 00:10:16,574
That's the spirit, sweetheart!

150
00:10:17,533 --> 00:10:19,243
That's why I love you.

151
00:10:20,661 --> 00:10:22,788
Is it because I look like

152
00:10:23,914 --> 00:10:25,499
the ultimate leading man?

153
00:10:27,460 --> 00:10:31,672
And because you make me believe in things

154
00:10:31,756 --> 00:10:34,258
that even I struggle to believe.

155
00:11:08,626 --> 00:11:10,044
More, Angge.

156
00:11:10,127 --> 00:11:11,921
Easy now. It's hot.

157
00:11:12,004 --> 00:11:14,298
We don't want it burned.

158
00:11:15,883 --> 00:11:17,551
Okay.

159
00:11:17,635 --> 00:11:18,928
You should put it there.

160
00:11:19,011 --> 00:11:19,929
Tess.

161
00:11:20,805 --> 00:11:22,139
We have visitors.

162
00:11:26,227 --> 00:11:29,772
Here, put this in a box.
Careful, it's hot.

163
00:11:29,855 --> 00:11:30,731
Okay.

164
00:11:31,690 --> 00:11:33,984
Angelito, where are the drinks?

165
00:11:34,068 --> 00:11:35,277
- Mom!
- The--

166
00:11:35,361 --> 00:11:37,613
- There it is!
- Coming right up.

167
00:11:37,696 --> 00:11:38,906
Thank you very much!

168
00:11:38,989 --> 00:11:42,201
Bechay, come here and hold this.

169
00:11:42,284 --> 00:11:43,285
Okay.

170
00:11:44,662 --> 00:11:45,913
Take care, Betch.

171
00:11:55,381 --> 00:11:56,382
Chief!

172
00:11:56,924 --> 00:12:01,178
- Let's drink later.
- Hi, Miss Tess!

173
00:12:11,355 --> 00:12:14,442
- Hello. Would you like some torta?
- Hello. Good afternoon.

174
00:12:22,908 --> 00:12:24,660
Go ahead and eat.

175
00:12:24,743 --> 00:12:25,995
- There.
- Thank you, ma'am.

176
00:12:26,078 --> 00:12:27,204
- Here.
- Thank you.

177
00:12:27,288 --> 00:12:28,789
Oh no, this is enough, really.

178
00:12:28,873 --> 00:12:32,168
You need something to wash
it down with when you're eating.

179
00:12:32,251 --> 00:12:33,461
- Right?
- True.

180
00:12:33,544 --> 00:12:36,630
And so people will know
that you're our customers.

181
00:12:36,714 --> 00:12:37,548
- Right?
- Yes.

182
00:12:38,674 --> 00:12:39,842
That's right.

183
00:12:39,925 --> 00:12:42,928
Why do people need to see
that we're your customers?

184
00:12:43,012 --> 00:12:44,430
Is there a problem?

185
00:12:44,513 --> 00:12:47,850
Oh dear, this stays between us, okay?

186
00:12:47,933 --> 00:12:52,813
But our folks here are on heightened alert

187
00:12:52,897 --> 00:12:56,317
because there are
so many people lurking around.

188
00:12:56,400 --> 00:12:59,195
We don't like outsiders.

189
00:12:59,278 --> 00:13:00,988
Of course, you know there are a lot

190
00:13:01,071 --> 00:13:07,369
of land grabbers, family snatchers,
dog grabbers, cat grabbers.

191
00:13:07,453 --> 00:13:08,662
Right?

192
00:13:08,746 --> 00:13:12,166
They're there! Come on. Say hi!

193
00:13:15,252 --> 00:13:16,086
See?

194
00:13:16,837 --> 00:13:20,966
Of course, I wouldn't want you
to get beaten up

195
00:13:21,550 --> 00:13:23,427
because you're outsiders.

196
00:13:23,511 --> 00:13:28,015
But I know you're close to Mikoy, right?

197
00:13:28,098 --> 00:13:31,310
All right, go ahead and eat.
I still have a lot to do.

198
00:13:31,393 --> 00:13:32,269
Come on, Bechay.

199
00:13:32,353 --> 00:13:33,938
- Thank you.
- Enjoy your meal.

200
00:14:00,965 --> 00:14:03,842
Sir, we both know why you're stressed.

201
00:14:04,510 --> 00:14:06,220
And it's not because of your phone.

202
00:14:16,313 --> 00:14:18,148
I can't stop worrying.

203
00:14:27,658 --> 00:14:32,413
And I know she talked to you
before she disappeared.

204
00:14:34,248 --> 00:14:36,041
And for some reason,

205
00:14:36,125 --> 00:14:38,878
she trusts you.

206
00:14:43,299 --> 00:14:46,302
What do I need to know?

207
00:14:49,471 --> 00:14:50,848
Honey!

208
00:14:51,390 --> 00:14:52,850
Honey, hurry!

209
00:14:53,601 --> 00:14:54,852
- Honey.
- Why?

210
00:14:55,811 --> 00:14:58,272
Is it an emergency? I'll get my gun.

211
00:14:58,355 --> 00:15:01,358
Why would we need a gun?
And why are we whispering?

212
00:15:01,442 --> 00:15:03,527
Because I think the G.A.G.O.

213
00:15:03,611 --> 00:15:07,197
still haven't stopped looking
for Mikoy and Chiara.

214
00:15:11,660 --> 00:15:12,578
What is it, Bok?

215
00:15:13,495 --> 00:15:14,788
Do you really think Mikoy is here?

216
00:15:14,872 --> 00:15:18,959
Because we might not be able
to handle the backlash.

217
00:15:19,960 --> 00:15:23,881
They won't do anything to us
if we talk to them properly.

218
00:15:23,964 --> 00:15:27,009
And there's only one way to find out
if Mikoy and Chiara are really here.

219
00:15:30,012 --> 00:15:31,472
There you go again, Bok.

220
00:15:40,856 --> 00:15:44,234
I was the last person La Fornarina
spoke to before she disappeared.

221
00:15:45,110 --> 00:15:46,362
Along with Mikoy.

222
00:16:10,094 --> 00:16:11,679
Where did they go?

223
00:16:19,228 --> 00:16:20,145
Let me do the talking.

224
00:16:20,229 --> 00:16:21,355
I'll do the talking.

225
00:16:21,438 --> 00:16:22,982
I want everything to come from me.

226
00:16:23,857 --> 00:16:25,025
- Wait. Hold it!
- Hold it.

227
00:16:25,109 --> 00:16:26,652
- Hold it!
- Hey, hey, hey!

228
00:16:26,735 --> 00:16:27,611
You can't!

229
00:16:27,695 --> 00:16:29,196
- Stay here.
- No, no!

230
00:16:30,114 --> 00:16:31,907
- No!
- Sir, are you sure?

231
00:16:31,991 --> 00:16:33,033
I'll finish you off.

232
00:16:33,117 --> 00:16:34,868
- That's a bit much.
- Chief, let it go.

233
00:16:35,953 --> 00:16:36,787
Let it slide.

234
00:16:44,503 --> 00:16:46,380
How may I help you?

235
00:16:46,463 --> 00:16:47,548
To be honest, just like Mikoy,

236
00:16:47,631 --> 00:16:49,925
we don't want you getting involved
in all this trouble.

237
00:16:52,052 --> 00:16:54,054
But you flew to Cebu,

238
00:16:54,138 --> 00:16:55,681
to come all the way here.

239
00:16:56,390 --> 00:16:57,725
That already involves us.

240
00:16:58,392 --> 00:17:00,436
Because I'm desperate.

241
00:17:00,519 --> 00:17:03,355
So we had no choice
but to come here and talk to you.

242
00:17:04,314 --> 00:17:05,357
What for?

243
00:17:28,714 --> 00:17:33,093
"The above-named individual
is under active pursuit

244
00:17:33,177 --> 00:17:35,054
and is considered armed
and highly dangerous

245
00:17:35,137 --> 00:17:39,767
and capable of violent resistance.
All enforcement units are…

246
00:17:40,517 --> 00:17:45,189
directed to… and arrest…"

247
00:17:47,983 --> 00:17:51,695
But we can still keep Mikoy
from getting hurt if you help us.

248
00:17:57,284 --> 00:17:58,368
You know, I…

249
00:17:59,912 --> 00:18:01,705
I'm sorry, Agent Alex,

250
00:18:02,581 --> 00:18:04,833
but we don't know where Mikoy is.

251
00:18:07,377 --> 00:18:08,462
Mr. Mario.

252
00:18:09,546 --> 00:18:12,549
We wouldn't have come
all the way here if we thought

253
00:18:12,633 --> 00:18:14,134
you didn't know where Mikoy is.

254
00:18:17,054 --> 00:18:18,972
And like you, we only want
what's best for Mikoy's safety--

255
00:18:19,056 --> 00:18:20,390
Nonsense!

256
00:18:22,017 --> 00:18:25,646
You were the ones who approached him first
to make him part of your mission.

257
00:18:25,729 --> 00:18:27,856
You promised him protection.

258
00:18:27,940 --> 00:18:29,942
And now you're saying

259
00:18:30,651 --> 00:18:32,611
his safety is your priority.

260
00:18:33,195 --> 00:18:35,322
Do you think we sleep well at night?

261
00:18:35,989 --> 00:18:37,866
The answer is no.

262
00:18:40,244 --> 00:18:44,915
Not because every minute
we're thinking about Mikoy's condition.

263
00:18:47,918 --> 00:18:49,837
We don't know where Mikoy is,

264
00:18:50,420 --> 00:18:51,505
what he's doing,

265
00:18:52,089 --> 00:18:53,799
or whether he's with Chiara.

266
00:18:56,343 --> 00:18:57,219
So it's best

267
00:18:59,847 --> 00:19:01,014
if you leave.

268
00:19:03,308 --> 00:19:05,352
And don't drag my family into this.

269
00:19:07,437 --> 00:19:09,398
You heard what Mr. Mario said.

270
00:19:09,481 --> 00:19:10,524
- Leave!
- Go.

271
00:19:10,607 --> 00:19:14,236
- Go on. Leave!
- Leave this place!

272
00:19:14,319 --> 00:19:15,362
Come on.

273
00:19:15,445 --> 00:19:18,782
- Go on. Leave!
- Let's go.

274
00:19:18,866 --> 00:19:20,576
- Leave now!
- Let's go.

275
00:19:20,659 --> 00:19:21,493
There!

276
00:19:21,577 --> 00:19:22,995
All right, thank you.

277
00:19:44,224 --> 00:19:45,851
Maybe we just came at the wrong time, Bok.

278
00:19:45,934 --> 00:19:46,768
Bok.

279
00:19:47,853 --> 00:19:49,771
Let's try again another day.

280
00:19:49,855 --> 00:19:52,232
Let's give them time to trust us more.

281
00:19:52,316 --> 00:19:53,233
Bok.

282
00:19:57,362 --> 00:19:59,198
Maybe it's about time to give up on Mikoy.

283
00:20:03,452 --> 00:20:05,704
Out of more than 190 countries,

284
00:20:05,787 --> 00:20:08,457
they had over 190 options.

285
00:20:08,540 --> 00:20:12,920
Each country has different
security levels and policies.

286
00:20:13,003 --> 00:20:14,421
That means

287
00:20:14,504 --> 00:20:18,091
they're left with fewer than 30 countries
that are easier options.

288
00:20:18,675 --> 00:20:20,219
And if you're going to take
into consideration

289
00:20:20,302 --> 00:20:22,930
that I made Philippine passports for them,

290
00:20:24,139 --> 00:20:26,600
their options are further limited.

291
00:20:28,227 --> 00:20:29,937
But don't worry.

292
00:20:30,020 --> 00:20:32,689
Of course, to help them
move around safely,

293
00:20:32,773 --> 00:20:35,442
I made sure all their documents
were in order.

294
00:20:35,525 --> 00:20:37,069
Not just passports,

295
00:20:37,152 --> 00:20:40,572
but with supporting documents
and character descriptions.

296
00:20:40,656 --> 00:20:42,866
And sir, don't worry.

297
00:20:42,950 --> 00:20:45,035
Your daughter, Chiara, is smart.

298
00:20:45,118 --> 00:20:48,789
She knows exactly what to do
in situations like this.

299
00:20:48,872 --> 00:20:51,750
And Mikoy is incredibly resourceful.

300
00:20:51,833 --> 00:20:54,169
That's why they make such a perfect team.

301
00:20:58,382 --> 00:20:59,341
Come on.

302
00:21:12,521 --> 00:21:15,607
You know, sir, believe it or not,

303
00:21:15,691 --> 00:21:17,442
in this story,

304
00:21:17,526 --> 00:21:19,152
I'm Team MikChi.

305
00:21:40,007 --> 00:21:42,092
Sweetheart, what are you thinking about?

306
00:21:44,678 --> 00:21:47,639
I thought you were a world-class assassin.

307
00:21:47,723 --> 00:21:50,726
That you can figure out
your target with just one look.

308
00:21:50,809 --> 00:21:52,644
And now you can't read me?

309
00:21:55,897 --> 00:21:57,899
What I'm reading is

310
00:21:59,234 --> 00:22:00,986
that you're deeply in love with me.

311
00:22:01,820 --> 00:22:02,738
There!

312
00:22:02,821 --> 00:22:03,989
Exactly!

313
00:22:15,709 --> 00:22:18,170
Do you miss your mom and dad?

314
00:22:18,795 --> 00:22:20,172
Angelito?

315
00:22:21,006 --> 00:22:23,133
The simple bakery of Pinagpala.

316
00:22:29,347 --> 00:22:33,685
You know, I don't think
I can hide anything from you anymore.

317
00:22:33,769 --> 00:22:35,520
You know me too well.

318
00:22:35,604 --> 00:22:37,939
You know, sweetheart, you're like rain.

319
00:22:38,023 --> 00:22:41,401
I'm completely soaked by you.

320
00:22:45,155 --> 00:22:47,908
Sweetheart, I'm sorry.

321
00:22:48,533 --> 00:22:52,704
I'm sorry that I'm the reason
you're far away from your family.

322
00:22:52,788 --> 00:22:55,540
Come on, sweetheart. Don't apologize.

323
00:22:55,624 --> 00:22:58,585
I'm sure they understand
my decision, okay?

324
00:22:59,169 --> 00:23:01,463
They know that even if I'm far away,

325
00:23:01,546 --> 00:23:04,424
I'm still happy because I'm with you.

326
00:23:05,342 --> 00:23:07,469
Isn't that what really matters in life?

327
00:23:07,552 --> 00:23:11,348
That I'm happy with the decisions
and the life I've chosen.

328
00:23:11,932 --> 00:23:17,229
And let's just keep it under
the name Chiara Valtrovi.

329
00:23:17,312 --> 00:23:18,814
- Okay?
- Oh, please!

330
00:23:18,897 --> 00:23:21,108
- You, honestly!
- Why?

331
00:23:23,401 --> 00:23:27,364
You're so good with sweet, charming words.

332
00:23:27,906 --> 00:23:29,991
But just make sure

333
00:23:30,075 --> 00:23:32,702
you only use those moves on me!

334
00:23:32,786 --> 00:23:35,705
If I find out you're being sweet
to someone else,

335
00:23:35,789 --> 00:23:37,499
your eyes will be
the only thing without bruises!

336
00:23:37,582 --> 00:23:39,292
Come on, sweetheart.

337
00:23:39,376 --> 00:23:42,170
I don't know whether
to feel flattered or scared.

338
00:23:45,257 --> 00:23:47,384
But I'm sorry, sweetheart.

339
00:23:48,343 --> 00:23:52,556
I guess I'm just getting used
to this kind of life again.

340
00:23:53,181 --> 00:23:54,307
When I was in Prague, at least,

341
00:23:54,391 --> 00:23:57,018
I knew I could still go home.

342
00:23:57,936 --> 00:23:59,187
But now,

343
00:24:00,564 --> 00:24:03,108
I'm not even sure
if I'll ever see them again.

344
00:24:08,738 --> 00:24:10,365
I promise you.

345
00:24:11,074 --> 00:24:13,618
Even if we're far away right now,

346
00:24:13,702 --> 00:24:15,495
living in hiding,

347
00:24:16,454 --> 00:24:19,457
that doesn't mean
you'll never see your family again.

348
00:24:22,294 --> 00:24:24,713
You can look forward to the day

349
00:24:25,380 --> 00:24:28,466
when we'll all be one normal family.

350
00:24:29,050 --> 00:24:32,345
And we'll be together
with the people we love.

351
00:24:33,388 --> 00:24:35,223
You can count on that.

352
00:24:56,828 --> 00:24:58,788
Agent Alex, I have an update.

353
00:25:00,749 --> 00:25:03,543
Wasn't there an order for us
to monitor Viktor Valtrovi?

354
00:25:09,049 --> 00:25:11,051
So he's going to see Chiara?

355
00:25:13,428 --> 00:25:16,181
So I immediately obtained
his flight information.

356
00:25:17,807 --> 00:25:19,809
- Prague?
- No.

357
00:25:19,893 --> 00:25:21,102
Sicily?

358
00:25:21,186 --> 00:25:22,312
Not there either.

359
00:25:23,521 --> 00:25:25,106
- Then, where?
- Where?

360
00:25:25,190 --> 00:25:27,400
The Queen City of the South.

361
00:25:27,484 --> 00:25:28,652
Cebu City.

362
00:25:40,622 --> 00:25:41,665
Lookouts!

363
00:25:45,293 --> 00:25:46,169
Sir Mario!

364
00:25:46,836 --> 00:25:47,879
Sir Mario!

365
00:25:49,714 --> 00:25:50,548
Sir Mario!

366
00:25:50,632 --> 00:25:52,592
Sir Mario, a car just arrived.

367
00:26:08,566 --> 00:26:10,485
Bechay, Angelito, go upstairs.

368
00:26:48,106 --> 00:26:50,150
We miss you all very much!

369
00:26:51,735 --> 00:26:54,654
Viktor's here to fish
for information from the Pinagpala's.

370
00:26:54,738 --> 00:26:57,365
Or Viktor came to give them information.

371
00:26:57,449 --> 00:26:59,701
<i>Either way, we don't have access</i>
<i>to that information.</i>

372
00:26:59,784 --> 00:27:01,703
<i>It's either from Mario or Viktor.</i>

373
00:27:01,786 --> 00:27:06,875
<i>I know how to get information</i>
<i>from their family.</i>

374
00:27:09,961 --> 00:27:11,838
<i>Are you going to tell that to Agent Alex?</i>

375
00:27:12,922 --> 00:27:16,301
Wait, then she's going to find Mikoy.

376
00:27:16,384 --> 00:27:17,510
How about your love team?

377
00:27:18,136 --> 00:27:19,304
Sweetheart, are you okay?

378
00:27:19,387 --> 00:27:20,805
- I can't calm down.
- Is there a problem?

379
00:27:20,889 --> 00:27:22,349
<i>I got a bad feeling a while ago.</i>

380
00:27:22,432 --> 00:27:24,976
<i>I thought someone was following me.</i>

381
00:27:32,442 --> 00:27:34,652
- Why? What happened?
- Go on. Get dressed. Hurry!

382
00:27:34,736 --> 00:27:36,154
Wait, what's happening?

383
00:27:36,237 --> 00:27:38,531
We're running out of time.
We have to go now!

384
00:27:38,615 --> 00:27:39,741
They've found us!
